Inside, recruiters distribute tote bags filled with notebooks, pens, and business cards, as many students utilize kiosks to upload their resumes and sign up for interviews. International students queue for advice on visa sponsorship, while career counselors redirect students toward applicable industries and remind them to maintain eye contact and follow up with personalized emails. Workshops on networking etiquette are held in an adjoining classroom, and an engineering society offers a resume review table near the stage. As the day winds down, students exit with their tote bags, while volunteers begin stacking collapsed booths.

Many attendees carry resumes in branded folders, with HR teams jotting notes on tablets during introductions. International students seek visa sponsorship advice, while alumni offer pep talks about technical interviews. Workshops on networking etiquette are held in an adjacent classroom, and students sign up for same-day interviews from a whiteboard listing employers. Monitors near the exit display a post-event survey link. Towards the end of the event, volunteers stack collapsed booths and gather leftover brochures, while students exit carrying their tote bags filled with materials, chatting about positive experiences outside on the quad.

The lively atmosphere is enhanced by the aroma of coffee and catered snacks, drawing attendees to a lounge area where alumni volunteers offer advice on networking etiquette, visa sponsorship requirements for international students, and prepare students for technical interviews. Many students utilize kiosks to upload their resumes to the fair database, quietly rehearsing elevator pitches. As the event concludes, announcement chimes signal the final hour, prompting quick sign-ups for interviews, while volunteers begin stacking collapsed booths and gathering leftover brochures, in addition to prompting participants to complete a post-event survey.

Inside, the aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafts from a lounge area, where friends decompress outdoors in the quad, discussing responses from companies. A robotics startup draws attention with a small drone flying above its booth, and a data science company showcases a live dashboard of attendance. Students utilize kiosks to upload resumes and sign up for interviews, while career counselors provide tips on maintaining eye contact. As the day concludes, students exit with tote bags filled with notebooks, pens, business cards, and resumes collected from exhibitors, alongside a whiteboard highlighting same-day interview opportunities.

A standout robotics startup captivates attention with a small drone flying above its booth, prompting discussions among students about positive interactions with mission-driven nonprofits. International students queue for visa sponsorship advice, while career counselors assist uncertain attendees, reminding them to maintain eye contact. Workshops on networking etiquette are ongoing in an adjacent classroom. As the event wraps up, sign-up sheets for same-day interviews fill, volunteers begin to stack collapsed booths, and monitors near the exit display a post-event survey link, inviting attendees to a lunchtime pitch session. Before the fair, students lined up outside the gym in anticipation.
